getSubsystemMemoryManagerType

public static java.lang.String getSubsystemMemoryManagerType(org.eclipse.uml2.Package subsystem)
Get the type of memory management for the subsystem:
  • direct--no caching
  • cached--map-based caching
  • clustered--map-based caching with messaging
  • distributed--distributed caching (memcached)

Parameters:
subsystem - the UML2 package object representing the subsystem
Returns:
the memory management type

getSubsystemDistributedCachingSoftware

public static java.lang.String getSubsystemDistributedCachingSoftware(org.eclipse.uml2.Package subsystem)
Get the content of the tagged value TAGGEDVALUE_SOFTWARE from the DISTRIBUTED stereotype. If there is no DISTRIBUTED stereotype, the tagged value is null. If there is a stereotype but the tagged value is null, return "memcached", the default implementation.

Parameters:
subsystem - the UML2 package object representing the subsystem
Returns:
the tagged value

getExpiration

public static java.lang.Integer getExpiration(org.eclipse.uml2.Class dto)
Get the content of the tagged value TAGGEDVALUE_EXPIRATION from the PERSISTENT stereotype on a class DTO object. If there is no PERSISTENT stereotype, the tagged value is null. If there is a stereotype but the tagged value is null or 0 (this translation happens automatically), return Integer.MAX_VALUE, the default implementation. If the tagged value is -1, return 0 (immediate expiration, no caching).

Parameters:
dto - the UML2 class object representing the DTO
Returns:
the tagged value
